"{\"uid\": \"whatdidyousay.org-2024-07-31-olympic-christ-threatens-to-sue-critics-over-last-supper-backlash\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Read more athttps://jonathanturley.org/2024/07/31/olympic-christ-threatens-to-sue-critics-over-last-supper-backlash/  Barbara Butch, the LGBTQ activist who was the center figure in the controversial \\\"Last Supper\\\" Paris Olympic scene is threatening to sue those criticizing her.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 118, \"end\": 131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}, {\"begin\": 137, \"end\": 142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.9993080885409392, \"rank\": 0.0006727448702186246, \"text\": \"LGBTQ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch played the role (wearing a Christ-like halo) viewed by many as a spoof on Christ in the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The creators insist that they were going for a type of \\\"pagan party\\\" of Olympic gods and sent a message of tolerance.\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Art experts havesupported the creators and pointed to paintingsthat inspired the pagan motif.\", \"from\": 503, \"to\": 596, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That is not exactly what was seen by millions of Christians who were deeply insulted by the parody.\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 646, \"end\": 656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.663782505952494, \"rank\": 0.50651486155872, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The question is not the intent of the creators, but the intent of critics in denouncing the display and its participants.\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The threat of legal action would not be especially serious in the United States where opinion is given robust protection in both criminal and civil cases.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 887, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8289571617189936, \"rank\": 0.20633495454242062, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In France, however, free speech is in a free fall with the left pushing for the censorship and criminalization of an ever-expanding range of political and religious speech.\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 979, \"end\": 985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.5567721390715378, \"rank\": 0.7959727156646589, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony itself had some truly powerful and stunning elements.\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I enjoyed the mix of music and imagery as well as the effort to show the diversity of France.\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1303, \"end\": 1309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.5567721390715378, \"rank\": 0.7959727156646589, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, other elements were more divisive or excessive.\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1367, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, the producers decided to use the ceremony to feature such elements as three young people hooking up for a \\\"m\\u00e9nage \\u00e0 trois.\\\"\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With many families watching with kids, many of us thought the scene was inappropriate for such an event.\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1609, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it was the supper scene that led to protests from clerics and critics.\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While claiming a message of\\\"tolerance,\\\"the scene was taken as yet another slap at religious elements in society.\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That is a debate that has continued to rage, particularly on the Internet.\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Audrey Msellati, Butch's attorney, posted a statement on\\u00a0Butch'sInstagram accountthat the DJ and activist will seek legal action after being \\\"the target of an extremely violent campaign of cyber-harassment and defamation.\\\"\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 2101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1879, \"end\": 1885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\", \"score\": 0.9999942511450801, \"rank\": 5.748888150527825e-06, \"text\": \"Audrey\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\"}, {\"begin\": 1969, \"end\": 1971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 0.9999999970441422, \"rank\": 2.951734825498504e-09, \"text\": \"DJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is promising to file \\\"several complaints against these acts.\\\"\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Clearly, any direct and intentional threats of violence against Butch should be prosecuted, as they can be prosecuted in the United States.\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2294, \"end\": 2307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8289571617189936, \"rank\": 0.20633495454242062, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the French laws sweep far more broadly in criminalizing opinion and what I have called \\\"rage rhetoric.\\\"\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2322, \"end\": 2328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9709328817897618, \"rank\": 0.029912486169153537, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In France, such complaints are often criminal matters.\", \"from\": 2423, \"to\": 2477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2426, \"end\": 2432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.5567721390715378, \"rank\": 0.7959727156646589, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In my new book, \\\"The Indispensable Right: Free Speech in an Age of Rage,\\\" I discuss the collapse of free speech rights in France as well as other European countries.\", \"from\": 2478, \"to\": 2643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2600, \"end\": 2606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.5567721390715378, \"rank\": 0.7959727156646589, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This anti-free speech wave has now reached our shores.\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has many allies in our own anti-free speech movement.\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"American leaders such asHillary Clinton have actually enlisted the help of European censorsto seek to silence American citizens.\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2756, \"end\": 2764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999879182725, \"rank\": 1.177559485349565e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2788, \"end\": 2795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hillary_Clinton\", \"score\": 0.9999981308932735, \"rank\": 1.8691101781756957e-06, \"text\": \"Clinton\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hillary_Clinton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hillary_Clinton\"}, {\"begin\": 2866, \"end\": 2874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999879182725, \"rank\": 1.177559485349565e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once the cradle of individual liberty, France long agobecame a global leaderin the crackdown on free speech.\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 2994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2925, \"end\": 2931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.5567721390715378, \"rank\": 0.7959727156646589, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These laws criminalize speech under vague standards referring to \\\"inciting\\\" or \\\"intimidating\\\" others based on race or religion.\", \"from\": 2996, \"to\": 3123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, fashion designer John Galliano has been found guilty in a French court on charges of making anti-Semitic comments against at least three people in a Paris bar.\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3159, \"end\": 3167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Galliano\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.92141955025801e-29, \"text\": \"Galliano\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q3501317\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Galliano\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Galliano\"}, {\"begin\": 3195, \"end\": 3201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9709328817897618, \"rank\": 0.029912486169153537, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3286, \"end\": 3291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1504034801094477e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At his sentencing, Judge Anne Marie Sauteraud read out a list of the bad words used by Galliano to Geraldine Bloch and Philippe Virgitti, including using 'dirty whore\\\" in criticism.\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3322, \"end\": 3332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne-Marie\", \"score\": 0.9643472599959311, \"rank\": 0.036970852031470776, \"text\": \"Anne Marie\", \"types\": 