u00e9 rang hollow for many of us in the free speech community.\", \"from\": 4165, \"to\": 4271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The French leaders have long been hypocritical in claiming to support free speech, such asmarching in support of the Charles Hebdo magazineafter the massacre after cracking down on its editors and writers.\", \"from\": 4272, \"to\": 4477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4276, \"end\": 4282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9709328817897618, \"rank\": 0.029912486169153537, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4389, \"end\": 4396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9844537750868432, \"rank\": 0.01576768543735741, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the artistic director for the opening ceremony of the Olympics, clearly wanted to be provocative in these scenes.\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4479, \"end\": 4485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999998699423, \"rank\": 1.3010623343440555e-10, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He succeeded.\", \"from\": 4607, \"to\": 4620, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Clearly, such provocative elements will spur debate and discussion, including heated opinions.\", \"from\": 4621, \"to\": 4715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Use of criminal sanctions for those expressing opinion would make a mockery of the 